        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="row stepCont step31-cont">
            <h3 class="step-heading bg-lt-blue">Step 3: Employee Sponsorship Program</h3>
            <div class="step-body">
                <p>Extend a discount on wireless services to your customers’ employees.</p>
                <p>Your customers’ employees are Individual Responsibility Users (IRU), or AT&amp;T consumers who have individual service agreements and eligible plans for which they are financially responsible.</p>
                <p>In exchange for marketing the Employee Sponsorship Program to your customers, we’ll provide you with an incentive for newly activated mobile lines.</p>
                <p>The key to success in this program is to educate and promote its benefits to your customers and their employees. The resources on this page will assist you in promoting the sponsorship program.</p>

                <h4>To get started with the Employee Sponsorship Program, take these steps:</h4>
                <ul class="bullet-cir-list">
                    <!-- Robyn 5/26/16: PE Request C0524_0848 remove the span tag from the list items --> 
                    <li><div class="bullet-cir bg-blue">1</div><p>Sign the IRU Compensation Addendum and send it to your Channel Account Manager.</p></li>
                    <li><div class="bullet-cir bg-blue">2</div><p>Review Employee Sponsorship Launch Kit to understand how to get started in the program and the associated benefits.</p></li>
                    <li><div class="bullet-cir bg-blue">3</div><p>Click one of the buttons below to register your end customers. If you have already registered your customer and would like to make updates, please choose "Update Existing End Customer."</p></li>
                    <li><div class="bullet-cir bg-blue">4</div><p>Market the Employee Sponsorship Program to your customers’ employees with the Employee Sponsorship Editable Templates.</p></li>
                    <li><div class="bullet-cir bg-blue">5</div><p>Keep it on the agenda and create a strategy with your customers for continued engagement.</p></li>
                    <!-- END Robyn 5/26/16 -->
                </ul>
                
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary pull-right updateCustomer" data-target="#IRU_RegisterCustomer">Update Existing End Customer</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary pull-right IRUMultipleCustomers" data-target="#IRU_RegisterMultipleCustomers">Register Multiple End Customers<BR /><span class="min5">(Minimum 5)</span></button>                                
